# Theme & tokens

## Source of truth

| Piece             | Path                             | Role                                         |
| ----------------- | -------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Token definitions | `src/theme/tokens.cjs`           | Colors, typography, spacing, radius, shadows |
| Generated CSS     | `src/theme/theme.css`            | `@theme` block for Tailwind v4               |
| Generate script   | `scripts/generate-theme-css.mjs` | `tokens.cjs` â†’ `theme.css`                   |

**Workflow after token changes:**

1. Edit `src/theme/tokens.cjs`
2. Run `pnpm generate:theme` (also runs on `prebuild`)
3. If typography changed â†’ sync `TYPOGRAPHY_TEXT_SIZES` in `src/lib/utils.ts`
4. Document semver impact in CHANGELOG if class names change

## Using tokens in components

Use **theme utilities**, not default Tailwind palette:

| Token kind | Examples                                   | Avoid                             |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| Typography | `text-h1`, `text-body-2`, `text-caption-1` | `text-2xl`, `text-sm`             |
| Colors     | `bg-primary-600`, `text-destructive-600`   | `bg-blue-500`                     |
| Radius     | `rounded-8`, `rounded-12`                  | `rounded-lg`                      |
| Shadows    | `shadow-secondary`                         | arbitrary shadow strings          |
| Spacing    | `gap-12`, `p-24`, `h-36`                   | numbers = **pixels** in our scale |

**Typography responsive scale:** mobile sizes in `theme.css`; desktop sizes kick in at **`md` (768px)** for `h1`â€“`h6`, `body-*`, `caption-*`.

**One-off Figma colors** not in the system: `bg-[#1A2B3C]` is OK. If the same hex appears in multiple components, promote to `tokens.cjs`.

**Responsive component APIs:** use `Responsive<T>` + `responsiveClasses()` from `@/lib/responsive` â€” see `atoms/text/`.

Token renames affect consumer CSS â€” often **major** semver if apps use those class names.

## Consumer theme-only setup

Consumers compile CSS locally. They do **not** import pre-built `styles.css` in new apps.

```css
/* consumer src/index.css */
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "@sporteev/sporteev-components/theme.css";
@import "@sporteev/sporteev-components/tailwind-source.css";
```

## JIT / static class strings (critical)

Consumer Tailwind scans `src/components/` and `src/lib/` via `@source`. Every utility in component code must be discoverable at build time.

**Allowed:**

```ts
const SIZE_CLASSES: Record<Size, string> = {
  s: "h-32 px-12 text-body-2",
  m: "h-36 px-16 text-body-1",
};
className={cn(SIZE_CLASSES[size], className)}
```

**Forbidden:**

```ts
// Dynamic template â€” JIT cannot see these utilities
className={`bg-${color}-600`}
className={colorMap[color]}  // if colorMap is built dynamically at runtime
```

Every key in `Record` maps must be a **static string literal**. Enumerate all variant Ă— color cells explicitly (see `atoms/button/variants.ts`).

## Class composition

```ts
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

className={cn(BASE_CLASSES, SIZE_CLASSES[size], variantClasses, className)}
```

Rules:

- Always `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` â€” not raw `clsx`
- Consumer `className` **last** so `tailwind-merge` resolves conflicts
- Per-size dimensions belong in `sizes.ts`, not inline in the component
- Spacing: `gap-12` = 12px, `p-24` = 24px

## Interactive states (default color ramp)

Unless Figma specifies otherwise, per semantic color (`primary`, `secondary`, `destructive`, â€¦):

| State   | Shade         | Background example      | Text-on-tint example      |
| ------- | ------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Resting | `{color}-600` | `bg-primary-600`        | `text-primary-600`        |
| Hover   | `{color}-700` | `hover:bg-primary-700`  | `hover:text-primary-700`  |
| Active  | `{color}-800` | `active:bg-primary-800` | `active:text-primary-800` |

Reference: `atoms/button/variants.ts` â€” each cell is a full static string including hover/active.

**Other states** (define in `variants.ts` or `field-styles.ts`):

| State      | Convention                                                                |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Focus      | `focus:outline-none` + ring or border; fields: `focus:border-primary-600` |
| Disabled   | Separate branch + `pointer-events-none`; grey tokens (`bg-grey-300`)      |
| Error      | `border-destructive-600` + `errorMessage` prop on fields                  |
| Transition | `transition-colors duration-150` unless Figma says otherwise              |

## Multi-node & field styling

**Multi-node components** (Modal, Toast): don't overload root `className` for inner nodes.

| Node         | className prop     |
| ------------ | ------------------ |
| Overlay      | root `className`   |
| Panel / body | `contentClassName` |
| Label        | `labelClassName`   |
| Input        | `inputClassName`   |

Reference: `molecules/modal/modal.tsx`, `molecules/input-text/field-styles.ts`.

**Icons inside components:** size via wrapper in `sizes.ts` + `[&_svg]:size-full` on wrapper. Consumers don't pass `className="size-full"` on icons inside DS components â€” but **Storybook** passes `className="size-full"` on icons used as story props (Button `startIcon`).

## Field pattern

Form fields share `FieldShell` + `field-styles.ts`:

- `label`, `helperText`, `errorMessage` props
- Error state: `border-destructive-600`
- Size tokens: `s | m | l` (fields may omit `xl`)

Reference: `molecules/input-text/`.
